<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <head>
    <title>Twitter Streaming Groups</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/top.css" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/icons/favicon.ico" />
    <script src="/top.js" type="text/javascript"><!--  --></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="logon">{{>div.logon.html}}
    </div>
    <div class="block">
      <h1>Help</h1>

      <p> This bot scans the favorites of its owners and retweets them
        on its own account, producing an independent twitter stream
        for the group of source owners.  </p>

      <p> Twitter bot command format
        <pre>command [@name] #{{=twitterId}}</pre>
        This bot only responds to its owners -- otherwise known as
        "source" users -- and only to correctly formatted commands.
        </p>

      <p> Commands' summary
        <table border="0">
          <tr>
            <td><code>help</code></td><td>Link to this page</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>stats</code></td><td>Current health report</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>sources</code></td><td>List owners</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>source @name</code></td><td>Add new source user</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>drop @name</code></td><td>Drop existing source user</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </p>

      <p> The bot's twitter account is <a href="/target">configured
        here</a> (admin).  </p>

    </div>
    <div class="copyrights">
    </div>
    <div class="logo rhs" onclick="javascript:document.location = 'http://gap-data.appspot.com/'; return true;">
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
